solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string greatestLetter(string s) {
        bool lower[26] = {false};
        bool upper[26] = {false};
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') lower[c - 'a'] = true;
            else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') upper[c - 'A'] = true;
        }
        for (int i = 25; i >= 0; --i) {
            if (lower[i] && upper[i]) {
                return string(1, 'A' + i);
            }
        }
        return "";
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass to mark presence of each letter in both cases, then scan backwards from 'Z' to 'A' to find the greatest letter with both cases present. Uses only two fixed-size boolean arrays.

